optimalDecisionValue.description:
The optimal decision is the difference between the most optimal value and the second most optimal value.
The most optimal value is set to what is recommended and the second most optimal value is the highest of the
two remaining options as shown in pseudo code below:
```
if (recommendation == GO_FOR_IT) {
  most_optimal_value = goForItExpectedValue
  second_optimal_value = max(winProbAfterPunt, fieldGoalExpectedValue)
} else if (recommendation == PUNT) {
  most_optimal_value = winProbAfterPunt
  second_optimal_value = max(goForItExpectedValue, fieldGoalExpectedValue)
} else if (recommendation == FIELD_GOAL) {
  most_optimal_value = fieldGoalExpectedValue
  second_optimal_value = max(goForItExpectedValue, winProbAfterPunt)
}
```

difference.description:
The difference between coach's decision to the second choice.
The actual and second choice are determined as shown in pseudo code below:
```
if (coachDecision == PUNT)) {
    actual = winProbAfterPunt
    secondChoice = max(fieldGoalExpectedValue,goForItExpectedValue)
} else if (coachDecision == FIELD_GOAL) {
    actual = fieldGoalExpectedValue
    secondChoice = max(winProbAfterPunt, goForItExpectedValue)
} else if (coachDecision == GO_FOR_IT) {
    actual = goForItExpectedValue
    secondChoice = max(winProbAfterPunt, fieldGoalExpectedValue)
}
```

optimalDecisionValue.description:
The optimal decision is the difference between the most optimal value and the second most optimal value.
The most optimal value is set to what is recommended and the second most optimal value will be the other choice.
```
if (recommendation == "two_point") {
  optimalDecisionValue = twoPointExpectedValue - xpExpectedValue
} else {
  optimalDecisionValue = xpExpectedValue - twoPointExpectedValue
}
```

difference.description:
The difference between what actually occurred in the play to the second choice.
```
if (play == xp_play) {
  difference = xpExpectedValue - twoPointExpectedValue
} else { // two-point play
  difference = twoPointExpectedValue - xpExpectedValue
}
```
